<HEADLINE>
FT  03 JUN 94 / International Company News: Corning adds to science business
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Corning, the US specialty glass and laboratory services group, is acquiring
Nichols Institute, a clinical testing company, in a deal valued at about
Dollars 325m, Reuter reports from New York.
Corning, which will merge California-based Nichols Institute with its
Corning Life Sciences unit, is paying Dollars 13 for each Nichols share.
Mr Albert Nichols, chairman of Nichols and holder of about 60 per cent of
the outstanding shares of the company, said he would vote in favour.
