FT  03 JUN 94 / UK Company News: Hambros Insurance falls 15%
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD LAPPER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Hambros Insurance Services yesterday blamed a poor performance by its loss
adjusting business for a 15 per cent decline in pre-tax profits to Pounds
8.3m for the year to March 31.
The decline in profits was foreshadowed at the interim stage.
The results covered the group's first complete year of trading and compared
with Pounds 9.8m on a pro forma basis.
The group said that loss adjusting had 'suffered from the exceptionally low
level of claims experienced by the insurance industry'. Turnover for the
division declined to Pounds 38.6m (Pounds 41.6m), but profits fell by more
than 50 per cent to Pounds 2m (Pounds 5m).
Hambros said it was reviewing the structure and cost base of its loss
adjusting operation in order to identify areas where its services could be
improved and broadened.
By contrast, Hambros' other businesses all performed well. Hambro Legal
Protection - which sells legal expenses insurance and telephone helplines
services - increased profits by 34 per cent to Pounds 4.5m, with turnover
rising to Pounds 12.9m (Pounds 9.9m).
Beale Dobie, which trades second hand endowment policies, increased profits
by 17 per cent to Pounds 1.4m with turnover ahead to Pounds 20.4m (Pounds
14.9m).
Earnings fell to 7.8p (11.2p). A proposed final dividend of 3.7p makes a
5.55p total.
