FT  03 JUN 94 / UK Company News: Enterprise North Sea field reaches peak
output
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT CORZINE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Enterprise Oil, the UK's largest independent explorer, yesterday announced
that its Nelson field in the North Sea had achieved peak production of
160,000 barrels a day only four months after the platform produced its first
oil.
Enterprise, which is locked in a hostile bid battle for Lasmo, the second
largest company in the exploration sector, has been labouring under
financial constraints. The Nelson field is its largest project to date. It
is also the first time that it has operated a North Sea platform.
Part of Enterprise's justification for the bid has been that it can use
Nelson's strong cash flow to bring forward Lasmo projects that might
otherwise be delayed by a lack of financing.
Mr Mark Hope, general manager, said the rapid move to peak production had
been achieved in large part by pre-drilling eight wells, which were ready to
flow once the platform was operational.
Additional wells were being drilled from the platform.
</TEXT>
