<HEADLINE>
FT  03 JUN 94 / People: Bodies Politic - Confederation of British Industry
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Lennart Aberg, md of Bayer UK; Brian Baldock, deputy chairman of Guinness;
John Banfield, chairman of Mobil Oil; Jean-Claude Banon, group md of General
Utilities; Michael Brinton, chairman of Brintons; Sir trevor Chinn, chairman
and md of Lex Service; Geoffrey Higham, chairman of The Rugby Group; Terry
Holmes, director of corporate affairs at Nestle UK; David Jefferies,
chairman of The National Grid; Aodh O'Dochartaigh, director of communication
at Bass; Ian Ramsay, md of CPC (UK); Howard Robinson, chief executive of
Calor Group; Peter Sanguinetti, director of corporate affairs at British
Gas; Colin Sharman, senior partner at KPMG Peat Marwick; David Teague, md of
ICL (UK); and Nigel Thompson, director of Ove Arup Partnership, have joined
the national council of the CONFEDERATION OF BRITISH INDUSTRY.
