FT  03 JUN 94 / Commercial rents 'increase 0.8%'
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Commercial property rents have risen for the first time since 1990, figures
published by Hillier Parker, chartered surveyors, show.
This is further evidence of a recovery in the rental market. Average
property rents have risen by 0.8 per cent over the past three months. Office
rents showed the strongest increase, with a rise of 1.6 per cent. Rents in
the retail sector have edged up by 0.1 per cent.
