<HEADLINE>
FT  03 JUN 94 / Tradepoint requests exchange status
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALISON SMITH
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Tradepoint Financial Networks, set up to develop an electronic share-dealing
system, has applied to City regulators to become a recognised investment
exchange.
Tradepoint is authorised as a service company regime, but becoming a
recognised exchange would put it on the same regulatory basis as other
exchanges such as the London Stock Exchange and the London Metal Exchange,
the company said yesterday. The change carries greater regulatory
obligations, and higher regulatory fees.
Mr Peter Bennett, chief executive, said the move would make it more easily
recognisable to participants and enable it to deal on a 'peer to peer' basis
with other exchanges.
The new system is aimed at institutional investors and will be
'order-driven'.
It will automatically match volumes and prices of share orders from buyers
and sellers, in contrast to the quote-driven system that dominates the Stock
Exchange, based on intermediaries' quotes.
</TEXT>
