FT  03 JUN 94 / New Independent editor sought
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A replacement is being sought for Mr Andreas Whittam Smith as editor of The
Independent, the loss-making national daily newspaper.
The search has begun, partly at least, because senior journalists at the
paper have been individually approaching the main shareholders warning that
editorial renewal will not be possible without changes at the top.
In an unprecedented move the journalists on the papers yesterday passed
overwhelmingly a motion of no confidence in the two main founders Mr Whittam
Smith and Mr Matthew Symonds.
