FT  02 JUN 94 / International Company News: Negara sells MAS stake
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KIERAN COOKE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   KUALA LUMPUR
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Bank Negara, Malaysia's central bank, has sold its shareholding in Malaysia
Airlines (MAS), the national carrier with the exception of one 'golden
share', writes Kieran Cooke from Kuala Lumpur.
It sold 11.5 per cent of MAS to the state run Pensions Trust Fund at the
beginning of this year.
